The trial of Mark Zinde, who is accused of killing his mother former SABC board member Hope Zinde has been postponed to the 15th June 2017.Zinde made a brief appearance at the Pretoria High Court briefly on Monday.Mark is accused of Hope&#8217;s murder that took place in 2016 at their home at the Peacanwood Estate. Her lifeless body was discovered in the boot of a car and it is believed that she had been killed days before her body was discovered. Mark was released on R10 000 bail in September 2016, however, the state sent him back to prison after the incident.Another charge of assault had been laid against him by his father who alleged that his son had attacked him during while out on bail.Mark is also facing a charge of possession drugs.-TNA Reporter 